column1: ## Van Noten et al. JOSE - Electronic Supplement S1: HVSR information of ambient noise measurements above boreholes in Brussels
#Nr: number
#Location: town of measurement in Belgium
#ID: Identification number
#Easting: location in Lambert72 coordinates
#Northing: location in Lambert72 coordinates
#lon: longitude in WGS84
#lat:latitude in WGS84
#Z (DEM): altitude of measurement deduced from DEM
#Geology: Cover geology of the location (see paper)
#Group: Group number of the location (see paper)
#Boreholenr: official nr of the borehole above which the measurement was performed (from Geological Survey of Belgium; https://gisel.naturalsciences.be/gisel/gisel.html)
#h: sediment thickness above the bedrock
#Top_bedrock: Z_DEM - h
#H/V file: Filenumber of raw ambient noise data file (available upon request)
#f0 min: f0_win/stddev (from GEOPSY)
#f0_win: average resonance frequency by taking the f0 of each individual window and averaging all f0 values from these windows (from GEOPSY)
#f0 average: scanning the average curve and identifying the frequency at which the maximum amplitude occurs (from GEOPSY)
#f0_ip: resonance frequency computed after interpolating the HV-Amplitude graph using python (see paper)
#error: standard deviation on f0 (from GEOPSY)
#f0 max: f0_win.stddev (from GEOPSY)
#A0: maximum amplitude (from GEOPSY)
#nw: number of windows (from GEOPSY)
#Vs: 4.f0_ip.thickness (Fig. 7)
#a_R1_R2_R3: a powerlaw relation value of group R1, R2, R3, R4 (= geologically-dependant PR)
#b_R1_R2_R3: b powerlaw relation value of group R1, R2, R3, R4 (= geologically-dependant PR)
#Th_Indiv: predicted sediment thickness after applying PR R1, R2, R3, R4
#Th-Th_indiv: difference between True thickness (from borehole) and predicted thickness (from PR R1, R2, R3 or R4; Fig. 6A)
#a_R: a powerlaw relation value of group R (= regional-dependant PR)
#b_R: b powerlaw relation value of group R (= regional-dependant PR)
#Th_all: predicted sediment thickness after applying PR R' (Fig. 6A)
#Th-Th_all: difference between True thickness (from borehole) and predicted thickness (from PR R'; Fig. 6A)
#diff: difference between h-h_indic and h-h_all (Fig. 6B)
